Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "lois" in different forms and positions, with translations in English in parentheses:

1. *Lois* je danas spremna da igra fudbal. (*Lois* is ready to play football today.)
2. Na fakultetu su nam dali zadatak da pišemo eseje o *loisu*. (We were given an assignment to write essays about *lois* at the university.)
3. Da li si pročitao knjigu o *loisu* koju sam ti preporučio? (Have you read the book about *lois* that I recommended to you?)
4. Izvini, da li možeš da mi pozajmiš *lois* za nekoliko dana? (Excuse me, can you lend me *lois* for a few days?)
5. *Loisova* nova frizura izgleda fantastično! (*Lois's* new haircut looks fantastic!)
6. Kada je videla svog psa, *Loisa* se odmah obradovala. (When she saw her dog, *Lois* was immediately happy.)
7. *Loisov* tim je pobedio u finalu turnira. (*Lois's* team won the tournament final.)
8. Jelena je u *loisu* sa svojim dečkom otišla na romantični vikend. (Jelena went on a romantic weekend with her boyfriend in *lois*.)

Note: "Lois" is not a word in Serbian, so I assumed it is a proper noun and used it as such in the sentences above.